# Theme palette (Tailwind + `.dark`)

The app uses Tailwind with `@custom-variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));` in `src/index.css`. Scope dark styles with `dark:` on the root `.dark` element (or `class="dark"` on `html`/`body`).

**Use only shades derived from the hex values below**—no unrelated accent colors.

## Light theme (default)

| Role                                      | Hex       | Notes                                          |
| ----------------------------------------- | --------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Page / surface background                 | `#e5e7eb` | Primary canvas                                 |
| Heading text (page title, section titles) | `#E0E0E0` | Bold headings                                  |
| Body / secondary / labels                 | `#E0E0E0` | Descriptions, monospace labels, ancillary copy |

## Dark theme (`dark:`)

| Role                      | Hex                             | Notes                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Page / surface background | `#171d26`                       | Primary canvas — lighter, subtler than before; less heavy than `#101828` for a more open feel                                                                                                                           |
| Heading text              | **Gradient** based on `#eeb1fc` | For a lighter look, start with `from-[#eeb1fc]` and blend to `to-[#f5dafc]` or a white-tinted variant of purple for highlight, keeping it _within the same family_ (not a new hue). Use reduced intensity for subtlety. |
| Body / secondary / labels | `#e2e6ee`                       | Lighter/softer than before for higher contrast and airier mood (used instead of pure white for gentleness)                                                                                                              |

## Implementation hints

- Prefer **CSS variables** in `index.css` for backgrounds and text roles if the same tokens repeat, then reference them in components; otherwise Tailwind arbitrary colors like `bg-[#e5e7eb] dark:bg-[#171d26]` are acceptable.
- **Headings:** light = solid `#202b3b`; dark = `bg-gradient-to-*` + `bg-clip-text text-transparent` with a gentle purple gradient (see above).
- **Separators / borders:** use transparentized or mixed tints of palette hues—e.g. a translucent purple line under a header (`#eeb1fc` at low opacity over `#171d26`); avoid harsh high-contrast borders.
- **Monospace labels** (e.g. “Toggle Theme”): inherit body/label text color for the theme, only changing font family.

## Do not

- Introduce colors outside this system (e.g. default Tailwind `blue-500` for primary UI) unless mapping to a documented shade above.
- Store theme colors only in scattered magic strings long-term—centralize in `index.css` or a small theme map when adding new screens.
